Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the project

I successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 to dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with the new dependency and its transitive dependencies

### 2. Modified src/App.tsx
- Imported `SpeedInsights` component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Added the `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<PageTransition>` wrapper, just before the closing tag
- This ensures the Speed Insights tracking is active across all pages of the application

### Framework-Specific Approach
The project is a Vite + React application, so I followed the React-specific installation instructions from the official documentation:
- Imported the component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Added the component to the root App component

### Verification Results
✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ Linter passed with no new errors (npm run lint) - pre-existing errors in other files remain unchanged
✅ Test suite passed (6/7 test files, 28/29 tests) - one pre-existing test failure unrelated to this change

### Implementation Notes
- The SpeedInsights component is placed inside the PageTransition wrapper to ensure it's rendered on all pages
- The component requires no additional configuration - it will automatically start tracking metrics
- To see the metrics, the application needs to be deployed to Vercel and Speed Insights enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- The component is designed to have zero impact on page performance

All changes follow the existing code structure and patterns in the project.
